# Quick Reference: Vercel Environment Variables

Copy and paste these into your Vercel project settings (replace with your actual values):

## üî¥ REQUIRED Variables

```env
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/health-record-system?retryWrites=true&w=majority
JWT_SECRET=your-64-character-secret-here-use-crypto-to-generate
JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY=15m
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-different-64-character-secret-here
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY=7d
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_SECURE=false
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-gmail-app-password
EMAIL_FROM=National Health System <your-email@gmail.com>
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend.vercel.app
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend.vercel.app,http://localhost:3000
```

## üü° RECOMMENDED Variables

```env
REDIS_URL=redis://username:password@your-redis-host:port
QUEUE_REDIS_URL=redis://username:password@your-redis-host:port/1
THROTTLE_TTL=60000
THROTTLE_LIMIT=100
REQUEST_BODY_LIMIT=10mb
```

## üîµ OPTIONAL Variables (if using AWS)

```env
AWS_REGION=ap-south-1
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-key
AWS_S3_BUCKET=your-bucket-name
AWS_KMS_KEY_ID=your-kms-key-id
```

---

## üîê Generate JWT Secrets

Run these commands in terminal:

```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

Use the first output for `JWT_SECRET` and the second for `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET`.

---

## üìö Swagger Configuration

- **Default**: ENABLED (accessible at `/api/docs`)
- **To Disable**: Add `DISABLE_SWAGGER=true`

